<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06269</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT GRANTING AUTOMATIC CIVIL SERVICE SUB-PROFESSIONAL ELIGIBILITY TO GRADUATES OF FOUR YEAR COURSES IN COLLEGES OR UNIVERSITIES, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to provide an incentive for college students to finish their four year courses and enhance the capacity or competencies of graduates of four-year degree programs by automatically entitling them to a sub-professional civil service eligibility.
 
Intends to enable current but efficient, loyal, dependable and deserving government employees without civil service eligibility to acquire job security.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VIOLAGO, MICAELA S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-02-12</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (000 2020-03-03)</td><td>2. Del Mar (000 2020-11-12)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION ON 2020-02-18</td></tr></table>